1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:11,675
(2 Corinthians 12:2): St Paul declares, ‘I know a man who fourteen years ago was caught up into the third heaven; whether in the body or no I cannot tell: God knoweth.

2
00:00:11,625 --> 00:00:19,137
Now granting Paul was there at any time, then either body and soul both turned to spirit or else his soul took wing out of his body.

3
00:00:19,137 --> 00:00:27,187
It is certain that his soul left not his body, for she was giving life unto his body; she must then have seen God in her and herself in him.

4
00:00:27,187 --> 00:00:31,162
The soul has three powers: mind, will and rage.

5
00:00:31,162 --> 00:00:34,125
These three powers are in league with deity.

6
00:00:34,125 --> 00:00:37,050
Will cleaving unto God can do all things.

7
00:00:37,050 --> 00:00:41,512
God seized of his divinity bestows upon her power and fecundity.

8
00:00:41,512 --> 00:00:47,212
Mind cleaving to the Son knows with the Son; it knows with the Son when it is void of knowledge.

9
00:00:47,212 --> 00:00:52,162
The third power is the power of attack, which is connected with the Holy Ghost.

10
00:00:52,162 --> 00:01:02,637
This power is ever making for the source whence it proceeded forth and the Holy Ghost is its initiator into the eternal nature: it floods the secret chamber of the soul, and lo!

11
00:01:02,637 --> 00:01:07,200
she loses time and place in the eternal, in time transcending time.

12
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:12,750
But for the soul this is not enough: had she enough she would have time in lieu of her eternity.

13
00:01:12,750 --> 00:01:14,350
Let us not flag.

14
00:01:14,350 --> 00:01:25,512
Not ours the blame if, being ready and atoned in will, God hides himself so that we cannot do all things with him although he plays his part just as the sun gives out its light and fire gives out its heat.

15
00:01:25,512 --> 00:01:33,487
Woodapples cannot check the letting of their gall, but God contrives from time to time to reach out to the longing soul if he is very near to her.

16
00:01:33,487 --> 00:01:41,325
So let her, never doubting, with hearty longing, hail God frequently: ‘O Friend of me, how long am I to wait for thee?

17
00:01:41,325 --> 00:01:48,850
He says, to Christ was given a new name: one by the angel, another by St Paul, a third by his heavenly Father.

18
00:01:48,850 --> 00:01:51,850
The angel gave him the name Jesus Christ.

19
00:01:51,850 --> 00:01:56,550
Joseph and Mary called him by this name which signifies Weal of the World.

20
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:59,175
The name is given to the wounded soul.

21
00:01:59,175 --> 00:02:01,312
Alas, we are too frail!

22
00:02:01,312 --> 00:02:08,225
We should be well of our infirmities being raised up and gotten in; we should be raised if we were destitute and unattached.

23
00:02:08,225 --> 00:02:14,950
For the exalted spark wherein we see the light divine, that never parts from God nor is there anything between.

24
00:02:14,950 --> 00:02:20,287
What matter then if good and ill and pain betide, they do but touch the lower faculties.

25
00:02:20,287 --> 00:02:24,737
St Paul gave him three names and called him the reflection of the Father.

26
00:02:24,737 --> 00:02:28,987
He says, the wounded soul is given the mystic heavenly bread.

27
00:02:28,987 --> 00:02:31,550
Whence comes her wound?—From longing.

28
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:33,825
What is longing?—It is love.

29
00:02:33,825 --> 00:02:35,887
What is nobler than longing?

30
00:02:35,887 --> 00:02:44,637
What we pray God for humbly and with longing he durst not refuse: desire ablush with modesty he leads into the triple chamber of the Holy Trinity.

31
00:02:44,637 --> 00:02:52,000
Paul called him also the fecundity of the Father and the image in the Father, working with the Father to bring forth his Person.

32
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:57,962
Verily I say, the soul will bring forth Person if God laughs into her and she laughs back to him.

33
00:02:57,962 --> 00:03:11,287
To speak in parable, the Father laughs into the Son and the Son laughs back to the Father; and this laughter breeds liking, and liking breeds joy, and joy begets love, and love begets Person, and Person begets the Holy Ghost.

34
00:03:11,287 --> 00:03:14,287
In this wise does he travail with his Father.

35
00:03:14,287 --> 00:03:18,675
The third name he gave was, The Majesty of the Substance of God.

36
00:03:18,675 --> 00:03:25,750
Majesty is the essence of his divine substance, this substance being the elemental matter of the three Persons.

37
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:35,850
The soul is called majesty when she gives up mode: then she knows the Father and paternity, the Son and filiation, and the Persons of them twain she comprehends in unity.

38
00:03:35,850 --> 00:03:39,000
The Father gave him five names, ineffable.

39
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,237
God keep us every whit in him.

40
00:03:41,237 --> 00:03:42,900
So help us God.

41
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:43,837
Amen.
